ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar. Both describe the same surgical procedure and post-operative course for a patient with a bilateral cleft lip and severe nose deformity. They detail the initial surgery, the complications with the flap, the steps taken to address venous congestion, and the eventual successful outcome. The main difference is that the clinical note is more structured with sections labeled Subjective, Objective, Assessment, and Plan, while the initial description is more narrative.
